# Upstream Protection (Fork Only)

This repository is a **fork** of `spring-projects/spring-petclinic`. The upstream project is not ours.

## Git remotes

- Use **only** `origin` pointing at the Chris at Cursor fork: `github.com/chrisatcursor/spring-petclinic` (GitHub treats `ChrisatCursor` and `chrisatcursor` as the same org).
- **Do not** add an `upstream` remote to `spring-projects/spring-petclinic`.
- **Do not** `git fetch` or `git pull` from `spring-projects/spring-petclinic` or any URL that is not the fork.

## Pushing code

- **ONLY** push to the fork (`origin`).
- Before every push, run `git remote -v` and confirm fetch/push URLs are the fork, not `spring-projects/`.

## Pull requests

- **ONLY** open PRs whose **base** repository is `chrisatcursor/spring-petclinic` (or `ChrisatCursor/spring-petclinic`).
- **NEVER** open a PR against `spring-projects/spring-petclinic`.
- When using GitHub CLI: `gh pr create --repo chrisatcursor/spring-petclinic`

## Syncing

- To update from GitHub, use `git fetch origin` and merge/rebase from **`origin/main`** (or the appropriate branch on the fork).

## Verification before push or PR

```bash
git remote -v
# origin must show: github.com/chrisatcursor/spring-petclinic (or ChrisatCursor)
# must NOT show spring-projects/spring-petclinic
```
